# Pre-push: full check before code leaves the local machine.
# Runs the SAME `check` gate CI's `check` job runs
# (validate:data → validate:edge → validate:map → typecheck → typecheck:domain:strict
#  → lint → vitest → build). Slow (~30s) but catches most failures locally.
#
# To skip in an emergency: git push --no-verify
# (but only when you've already run `npm run check` locally and it passed).
npm run check

# CI also runs two jobs that `npm run check` does NOT:
#   - deno-tests : the edge-function type-check + execution tests (money-path
#                  signature verification, refund decisions). Run here via
#                  check:edge-behavior (deno task check:edge + test:edge) when Deno
#                  is installed, so a broken edge function is caught pre-push.
#                  `npm run check` itself deliberately EXCLUDES this to stay in
#                  lockstep with the CI `check` job (tests/build/ciCheckParity);
#                  the edge behavioral coverage lives here + in CI's deno-tests job.
#   - e2e        : Playwright Chromium + mobile-safari. Deliberately NOT run
#                  on every push (needs `npx playwright install` browsers + a
#                  dev server, ~minutes). Run it manually before risky UI
#                  changes: `npm run test:e2e`. CI is the backstop.
#
# So `npm run check` is a SUBSET of CI. With production deploying independently
# of CI today (see docs/DEPLOY.md "Gating production on CI"), do not rely on a
# green local `check` alone — let this hook finish and watch the Actions tab.
npm run check:edge-behavior
